    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "00d3e491deb2e906",
      "text": "A Collective Story Harvest enables us to deeply connect with and learn from the experience in our community, team or organization. A number of stories are shared in small groups and we work with a set of specific themes to harvest each story. Each of the participants either harvests one of the themes or is a witness during the storytelling and then shares back to the storyteller and small group. Finally, we come together to converge our learnings across all the stories."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "35c2d65352dd981f",
      "text": "We’ve found that group harvesting takes time – at least 90 minutes is the minimum time needed. Keeping the storytelling to around 30 minutes is advisable otherwise it is easy for listeners to become overloaded."
    },
